Here is a quote I’ve been discussing with my teenage boy as he starts dating and making big decisions. Decisions that can affect his future. The cool part is, it’s a quote from his great great grandfather. 

“The choices we make will affect the scope of our agency in the future. As of now, we have the right of decision. What we will have tomorrow depends upon how we decide today.” - Marion G. Romney

Try this great core based workout. 

EMOM for 10 or 20 or 30 minutes. 

Choose one carry and march it out for 60 seconds. 

- Suitcase Carry 
- Waiter Carry
- Crossbody Carry
- Racked Carry
- Farmer Carry

Choose a weight that challenges you but also allows you to march without resting it against your leg. 

The bells I used and had available to me were. 32kg and the doubles were 28kg 

Then drop down for a minute plank. Remember to keep it tight and drive those elbows towards your toes. 

Enjoy.

Brussel Sprouts w/ Bacon and Goat Cheese. 
Another one of my favorite unique side for Thanksgiving. 
This side was just enough for my family of 7. Obviously for a big group you can double or triple this. 

- 1 pound of Brussel Sprouts
- 5 slices of thick bacon 
- 2 oz or 1/4 C. Goat Cheese
Sauce
- 2 Tbsp of oil
- 1 Tbsp Honey
- 2 Tbsp Dijon Mustard
- 2 Tbsp Apple Cider Vinegar
- Salt 
- Pepper

Chop the of bottom and cut the Brussel sprouts in half. 
Dice the Bacon and cook till browned. 
Cook Brussel Sprouts in pan with bacon fat. 
Mix Sauce ingredients. 
Place Brussel Sprouts in dish. Add Goat cheese and sauces. Lightly mix together and enjoy.

While meditating this morning I was thinking about gratitude and envy. I was focusing on all that god has blessed me with and it reminded me of a talk I listened to back in October. 
The speaker said that the adversary rejoices in labels. They divide us and restrict the way we view ourselves. I have always struggled with self confidence and envious thoughts. 
Instead I need to focus on the labels that are true and matter. 
I am a husband, I am a father, I am a child of God!

We have a good stockpile of ground beef in the freezer so I’m always looking for good quick recipes using it. 
This is not a traditional taco but if it’s meat and in a tortilla shell I’m interested. 
This time we added micro greens on top to pack it with extra goodness. 

Thai Beef Tacos

Ingredients: Meat
* 1 1/2 lbs Ground Beef
* 1 Pepper
* 1 tsp Garam Marsala
* 2 cups Cilantro
* 4 cloves Garlic
* 1 tbsp Ginger
* 1/4 cup Green onions
* 1/3 cup Peanuts
* 1 Cucumbers
* 1/2 cup Thai Basil
* 1/3 cup Soy Sauce
* 1/4 cup Thai Chili Sauce
* 8 Flour Tortillas
* Micro Greens

1: Brown beef in skillet. Add Pepper, Ginger, Garam Marsala, and Garlic. Cook for another minute then add Soy Sauce, Thai Chili Sauce and some of the green onions. Keep some to top the taco later.
2: Chop produce and warm tortillas. 
3: Build taco.
4: Eat Taco!

Cowboy Steak Tacos

What makes them “Cowboy”? I made these on #cowboyfriday and every cowboy loves steak right? 

Steak Marinade

1.5 pounds flank steak
1/3 C Olive Oil
3 Tbsp Soy Sauce
1 Juicy Lime Juiced
1 Tbsp grated or Diced Garlic
1 Tbsp Cumin
1 Tbsp Chili Powder
1/3 C Vinegar

Mix ingredients together and let marinade 2 hours or overnight. 

Cook meat to desired doneness. 

Toppings: 
- Diced Onions and Cilantro
- Sliced Jalapeños 
- Sliced Radishes
- Microgreens (sends this into the healthy realm)
- More Limes
- My Favorite Tomatillo Salsa
